In a speech at the Capital Hilton in Washington, D.C., President Joe Biden praised mayors for their leadership and emphasized the importance of their role in solving real problems and improving people's lives. He highlighted the bipartisan effort to pass the infrastructure law and thanked mayors for their support in getting it done. Biden also discussed the American Rescue Plan and the impact it has had on communities, particularly through the allocation of $350 billion to state and local budgets. He urged mayors to use these funds to address challenges such as childcare, healthcare, climate change, and education. The President emphasized that the Build Back Better Act, which is currently being debated, will further alleviate pressure on families by making essential services more affordable and accessible. He also emphasized the need for the wealthy and big corporations to pay their fair share in taxes. Biden concluded by expressing his confidence in the American people and their ability to overcome challenges when they work together.